=== TREATMENT PRICING ===

Standard treatment rates (EUR):
- Examination: 45 (general physical; exotic pets may be 55)
- Vaccination: 35 (single vaccine -- Nobivac DHPPi+L4, Purevax RCP, Filavac)
- Surgery minor: 250 (under sedation -- foreign body, abscess, small mass)
- Surgery major: 600 (under general anesthesia -- orthopedic, splenectomy, complex GI)
- Dental cleaning: 120 (full scaling and polishing under sedation)
- Dental extraction: 85 per tooth (multiple extractions may be discounted)
- Blood work: 60 (CBC and biochemistry panel)
- Urinalysis: 40 (complete with sediment exam)
- X-ray: 80 per view (two views are standard for most diagnostics)
- Deworming: 25 (oral or injectable antiparasitic)
- Grooming: 40 (nail trim, ear cleaning, coat brushing)
- Emergency triage: 95 (intake assessment and stabilization, on top of treatments)


=== EMERGENCY SURCHARGE ===

Emergency visits outside regular hours (Mon-Fri 8:00-18:00) carry a 50%
surcharge on all treatment costs. The surcharge is already factored into
individual treatment costs when recorded -- do NOT apply it again at the
invoice level.


=== DISCOUNTS ===

Discounts are applied at the invoice level, not per treatment.

Multi-pet discount: 10% off the invoice subtotal when the owner has 2 or
more pets registered at the clinic.

Senior pet discount: 5% off the invoice subtotal when the pet is 10 years
or older at the time of the appointment. Calculate age from date_of_birth
relative to the appointment date.

Discounts do NOT stack. If both apply, use whichever gives the larger
discount amount.

Invoice formula:
  subtotal = sum of all treatment costs for the appointment
  discount = the larger of multi-pet or senior-pet discount (if eligible)
  final_amount = subtotal - discount


=== APPOINTMENT POLICIES ===

Default durations (minutes):
- Examination: 30
- Vaccination: 20
- Dental cleaning: 60
- Surgery minor: 90
- Surgery major: 180
- Emergency triage: 45

Use these when scheduling unless the veterinarian requests otherwise.

Scheduling: appointments can be booked up to 90 days in advance.

Cancellation: less than 24 hours notice incurs a 20 EUR fee. No-shows are
also charged 20 EUR. Record as a separate invoice.


=== VACCINATION SCHEDULE ===

Dogs:
- DHPPi (Distemper, Hepatitis, Parvo, Parainfluenza): first dose at 8 weeks, booster at 12 weeks, then annually
- Leptospirosis (L4): first dose at 8 weeks, booster at 12 weeks, then annually
- Rabies: first dose at 12 weeks, booster every 3 years

Cats:
- RCP (Rhinotracheitis, Calicivirus, Panleukopenia): first dose at 8 weeks, booster at 12 weeks, then annually
- Rabies: first dose at 12 weeks, booster every 3 years

Rabbits:
- Myxomatosis + RHD (Filavac): first dose at 10 weeks, booster annually


=== PAYMENT TERMS ===

Invoices are due within 14 days of the appointment. After 30 days, status
changes to 'overdue'.

Emergency treatments must be paid before discharge or within 7 days with
prior arrangement.

Accepted methods: cash, credit card, bank transfer.
